Gunmen last night invaded the residence of the Chairman of the Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU) of the Federal University, Gusau, Zamfara State, Malam Abdulrahaman Adamu, and abducted five family members. A source said the gunmen came to the residence of the ASUU chairman at Damba Quarters in a Gusau suburb shortly after midnight, fired shots and kidnapped a nephew, a niece and a brother of the ASUU chairman, including two of his sister in-laws. The gunmen also abducted another staff of the university attached to the bursary department, identified as Alhaji Abbas, in the Damba neighborhood. 